social_posts.post_text: 2022 shenanigans ✨making room for 2023✨happy new year one and all ✨

I had the extreme pleasure of speaking with my ‘sister in love’ Rooney Mara on LaunchLeft podcast to kick off the new year! Her authenticity, beauty and grace weren’t surprising to me but, through our conversation I came to know more about her work and her gentle spirit too, (which prompted me to make a real time adjustment to her rock ‘n roll spirit animal, ha!) @launchleft is an intentional space where artists can talk about their work, highlight other creatives and, discuss where art and activism meet. This episode hit every single feel for me. Plus it was adorable to see her blush when I asked if she’d alway had a crush on baby bro… 👻 Rooney launches one of my favorite change-maker businesses @suaysewshop- I spoke with powerhouse CEO and lead designer Lindsay about all things future/perfect/now. You can find it wherever you hear podcasts or go to LaunchLeft.com/podcast for audio/video options. Don’t forget to rate & subscribe to join the conversation! 
📸 Thomas Whiteside

Lately

What a night! LA’s first screening of “Fragments of Paradise” the award winning documentary on Jonas Mekas directed by KD Davison.  Known as the godfather of avant-garde cinema, this intimate portrait of Mekas was just what we needed to fill our cups. A singular and deeply influential artist, his personal story echoes the triumphs and struggles of all artists who transform their pain into art, joy and community.  We are grateful to have been a part of this special event that kicked off with a performance by @escapeartistlovers and a short film 'Bourn Kind’ by @racheldirects. Big ups to the audience for being so warm and receptive + the yum food by @veganafoodtruck.  A truly inspiring night made possible by the incredible generosity and support of @jenniferkhowell @theartofelysium and @artroomdtla.

Still reeling from the ‘beauty of the moment’ that was the “Fragments of Paradise” screening. The film, like the artist Jonas Mekas, was poetic, powerful, original and brilliant. Congratulations KD Davison and thank you for making this film! Also a very honorable mention to Chris Tucci for Designing + Animating the film, so so good! And last but not least, hardcore gratitude and appreciation to ms Jennifer Howell for joining me in celebrating KD and the film by making this special screening happen. 🗝️🗝️🗝️
Macky Spider Bowman

30 years 🕊️🙏🏼Celebrating River’s life today 🙏🏼🕊️

“It’s the smaller things, that make the bigger things, seem so much more rewarding. We’re all in this together. We can all do our part.” - River 

Sincerest gratitude to River’s fans! #givers4river 
And to the amazing artists who created these images of River, thank you. (I don’t know exactly who to tag so, please tag yourselves in the comments.) “River” album art @chris.tucci “Lost in Motion” painting @jackcoulter Aleka’s Attic album cover photograph @michaelstipe & thank you @kddavison333 for making this reel for me 🤍

LOVE is more powerful than hate. We can all do our part. More love. Less hate. Peace. Peace. PEACE. 
xxx Rain 

🤍🕊️🤍🕊️🤍🕊️🤍🕊️🤍🕊️🤍🕊️🤍🕊️🤍🕊️🤍

“I’ve learned that if you can’t get it all together to accomplish this thing called peace, you do at least your part in your life, because that’s where you can truly make an immediate difference.” ~ River Phoenix

“Vegetarianism is a link to perfection and peace. But it’s a small link. There are lots of other issues: apartheid, vivisection, political prisoners, the arms race. There’s so much going on in this world today, so much ignorance among people. That’s not to say I’m not standing amongst everybody. But the point is, what can we do now? That’s the thing about vegetarianism; it’s an individual’s decision and it’s something you have control over. How many things do we really have control over?” ~ River Phoenix

“It still strikes me as strange that anyone could have any moral objection to someone else’s sexuality. It’s like telling someone else how to clean their house.” ~ River Phoenix

“We’re all worth it, man. We’re all worth millions of planets and stars and galaxies and universes.” ~ River Phoenix

“Although I can’t stop all cruelty to living creatures on the planet, I can be kinder to every living creature in my life.” ~ River Phoenix

“I would never, never do anything unless I believed in it.” ~ River Phoenix

“Run to the rescue with love and peace will follow” ~ River Phoenix

away on a solo sojourn 
to the land where the sun hits first 
one witness
two views 
unimaginable beauty
untenable sorrow 
mountains and flowers 
warriors and cowards 
war is raging 
wails for peace 
the wind still wild 
the stars still bright 
still news of heartbreak 
thousands of children 
will not see another birthday 
and I so soon
to celebrate half a century
the mix of sadness and joy 
family, music, laughter, friends
confounded and confused
after all this time 
we still believe in violence
or maybe we just forgot
the source of all life
is love
